casebody.data:
James E. EACKLES, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. WD 81011 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: August 28, 2018 Natalie Hull Hoge, Assistant Appellate Defender, Kansas City, MO, Attorney for Appellant. Joshua D. Hawley, Attorney General, and Daniel N. McPherson, Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. Before Division Two: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, and Lisa White Hardwick and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Mr. James Eackles appeals from the judgment entered by the Circuit Court of Buchanan County, Missouri, denying his Rule 24.035 motion for post-conviction relief without an evidentiary hearing. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
